ue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marrakesh\", \"score\": 0.9999960995263463, \"rank\": 2.1433115643921766e-06, \"text\": \"Marrakesh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marrakesh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marrakesh\"}, {\"begin\": 217, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9857427602933898, \"rank\": 0.014402306435040875, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\", \"score\": 0.9495444254760872, \"rank\": 0.031041409007459622, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\"}, {\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Stahl_(game_designer)\", \"score\": 0.9999798565737097, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daniel Stahl\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Stahl_(game_designer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Stahl_(game_designer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Redshirting at Cal this spring to prepare for the Paris Games, Alekna delivered the winning throw of 231 feet, 11 inches (70.70 meters) \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 nearly 10 feet beyond what anyone else managed.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old Lithuanian's two next best throws \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 229-5 (69.94) and 225-4 (68.68) \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 also would have won the competition.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"score\": 0.9668707691641155, \"rank\": 0.015245855205627374, \"text\": \"Lithuanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI feel good.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m happy with my result \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 over 70 meters, that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I was hoping for,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Alekna told World Athletics the day after flying 6,000 miles from the Bay Area to Morocco.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999996631273119, \"rank\": 3.368726299264742e-07, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9857427602933898, \"rank\": 0.014402306435040875, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t as fresh but I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m happy with it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Alekna uncorked a world-record throw of 243-11 (74.35) last month to serve further notice that he will be a serious contender at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He finished second at the World Championships in 2022 as a 19-year-old, then wound up third at the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009923 Worlds.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was his first meeting of the year against Stahl (the 31-year-old Swede who won the Tokyo Olympics and owns two World Championship titles)\\u00c2\\u00a0 